The paper focuses on developing a practical algorithm for autonomous harvesting in the strawberry industry, which involves machine perception and economic viability. This suggests that the paper may fall under the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper explores the use of deep reinforcement learning, which is a popular area of research in Computer Vision (cs.CV), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper addresses the sub-objective of viewpoint optimization, which involves developing a control policy, suggesting that it may also fall under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
